<p>
SysDB is an Open Source project and puts a high emphasis on an open
development process. Any community contributions are highly welcome and there
are various ways to get involved by either <a
href="/download/#development">writing code</a>, <a
href="/documentation/">writing or improving documentation</a> or the website,
or spreading the word about SysDB and helping users.
</p>

<h2 id="help">Give and Get Help</h2>

<p>
Interactive help may be shared using any of these forums:
</p>
<ul>
	<li><b>Mailinglist:</b> the <a
		href="mailto:sysdb@sysdb.io">sysdb@sysdb.io</a> mailinglist provides
		an easy way for asynchronous communication. See <a
		href="/contact/#mailinglist">here</a> for more details.</li>
	<li><b>IRC:</b> the <a
		href="https://webchat.oftc.net/?channels=sysdb">#sysdb</a> channel on
		the <a href="ircs://irc.oftc.net:6697">irc.oftc.net</a> network may be
		used for real-time interaction with other users.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="talks">Spread the Word</h2>

<p>
Speaking about SysDB at conferences or other events is a great way to spread
the word about the project. Make sure to let us know if you did so, so we can
link your talk from this site.
</p>

